# Railway deployment

After completing code changes for this project, **commit and push to `main` automatically** to trigger Railway production deploy. Do not ask "Want me to deploy?" — just deploy.

## Workflow

1. Finish the requested change and verify build (`npm run build`) when practical.
2. Commit with a concise message (user did not need to ask for commits when deploying).
3. `git push origin main`
4. Confirm deploy with `railway status` (optional: curl the production URL).

## Production

- URL: https://tire-detection-production.up.railway.app
- Railway auto-deploys from `main` on push.

## Skip deploy only when

- User explicitly says not to deploy, or only wants local changes.
- Changes are docs-only / experimental and user asked to hold off.
- Push would fail (fix first, then deploy without asking).
